As the Senior Key Account Manager Chains you are joining one of the most dynamic teams at Booking.com (USA) Inc. You will be responsible for managing and expanding the partnership and the relationships with strategic partners with a global reach. Bring your passport and some comfortable shoes.
You will strive to achieve new levels of collaboration with this group of stakeholders by facilitating a joint company-strategic account planning process that develops mutual performance objectives, financial targets, and critical milestones for a medium and long term period.
You will deliver insights via enhanced data analysis, strategic account planning, and providing performance advice which will take the partner’s businesses to new heights. You will be working alongside a global team of colleagues who are equal parts passionate and knowledgeable about e-commerce and travel. This role represents the entire range of Booking.com BV products and services and ensures the assigned customers' needs are met by the company. You will find opportunities to drive value for your partners by identifying problems, offering creative solutions, and leveraging partnerships to move both organizations toward their strategic goals.
Our customer, the traveler, is the reason we do all this after all. You will be a member of a team dedicated to ensuring that our travelers have the best selection, offers and experience when they book with Booking.com.
To be successful in this role, you will need to demonstrate advanced communication skills to manage across different levels of stakeholders internally at Booking.com as well as within our partner organizations including up to C-level.  You will rely on your excellent interpersonal skills and previously demonstrated stakeholder management capabilities capabilities.  You have the proven ability to execute via enhanced strategic, comprehensive, result focused account plans to achieve success. Our clients are some of the best and brightest in the lodging industry, working with them will be both challenging and rewarding. They can tell if you are not having a good time. So, if you can do it all with a smile and a great attitude that is a huge plus.
Main responsibilities include but are not limited to:
Represent Booking.com BV’s-strategy and vision for strategic partners.
Advocate the Booking.com BV brand name and its credibility to strategic and across related industry associations.
Support Booking strategy and influencing initiatives and product development based on advanced global market knowledge and strategic partner relationships.
Prepare for and facilitate agreements on commercial terms regarding complex high value contracts between Booking.com and our strategic partners.
Closely coordinates company executive involvement across different stakeholder levels including C-level customer management.
Implementation of high value opportunities in alignment with company strategy, while uncovering solutions that lead to new opportunities for partner growth.
Train, consult, monitor, support, and guide internal stakeholders in managing the strategic and key partners in order to optimize and drive their performance.
Advocate Booking.com B.V. innovations/projects/products with strategic and key partners to enhance performance and unlock strategic business opportunities at a global level.
Implement in depth Account profiles and plans that show understanding of the complexity of the Account across their global business;
Analyze portfolios on multiple levels with the ability to gather insight and translate into actions at global, national and on local/property level;
Required Skills:
If you have 8-12 years’ experience in relevant roles with at least 5 years being in a Strategic or Key Account Management position  (preferably working in a global capacity) this may be the role for you;.
Experience working in a Hotel Group, Hospitality REIT, or Hotel Management company headquarters or regional level is a strong plus;
Strong knowledge of e-commerce and travel industry and related trends.
Capable to handle complex legal discussions;
Advanced project management skills;
Enhanced ability to read and interpret multiple data sources in order to define short/medium/long-term goals;
Ability to communicate clearly, verbally and in writing to just about anyone;
If you deliver presentations that keep people awake, excite them about the mission and have them leave the room with a clear understanding of the next steps on the road to success this may be the role for you;
A love of learning new things, an ability to think on your feet and an attitude that embraces change is a must;
If you are driven, volunteer for new challenges without being asked, and take ownership of your work plus you love a good puzzle this may be the role for you;
Fluent English speaker and writer;
Formal university education, hospitality focus is preferred, Master’s Degree a big plus;
Availability to travel up to 75% of the time. I told you to get comfortable shoes;
Excellent MS Power Point and Excel skills are a must;
Valid driver’s license is required.
