Financial Analyst – Financial Planning & Analysis team - Global Partner Services
At Booking.com, our mission is to make it easier for everyone to experience the world. And while restrictions have complicated travel over the past years, we evolve with our environment to facilitate people's experiences in a safe and responsible way. With strategic long-term investments into what we believe the future of travel can be, we are opening career opportunities that will have a strong impact on our mission.
Move beyond compiling data and help tell the story behind the numbers. This position offers the opportunity to drive financial decision making within Booking.com.
We are currently looking for an entrepreneurial Financial Analyst to be part of the dynamic and fast-paced Financial Planning and Analysis (FP&A) team, to support the Global Partner Services. In this role you will report directly to the FP&A Finance Manager for Global PS and will be based in Amsterdam.
You will work closely with the three regional FP&A teams to develop, implement and continue to improve on a reporting and insights strategy for our key metrics. With this strategy, you will need to push yourselves and others to go beyond reporting metrics, but also find and tell/present the stories that need to be told or actioned. In doing so you will bridge the gap between what the (financial) data tells us and decision making on a wide array of topics. 
You will be responsible for setting up collaboration with the three regional FP&A teams, building alignment where needed, challenge and further evolve metrics, building automated dashboards, forecasting, analyzing, and reporting the performance that is relevant for our stakeholders in Partner Services. 
Booking.com is a continuously evolving organization and with that, your tasks and duties will also evolve over time. You will be keen to develop and grow within the role and challenge yourself to take on additional projects and responsibilities as they present themselves.
B.responsible:
Play the pivotal role for FP&A across PS to tell the stories from and with data;
Present and tell the stories from that require action or have impact on other stakeholders;
Contribute to robust, scalable and insightful reporting of the key metrics;
Building insightful automated dashboards with business KPIs for the stakeholders;
Provide (financial) support and contribution to the region’s strategic decision making;
Continuously seek ways to improve existing reporting to fit with evolving requests from senior management;
Proactively deliver intelligence based on data and support and advise the business partners and regional colleagues whenever there is an opportunity;
Communicate proactively with managers in international markets to understand market/business trends;
Perform ad-hoc analysis, scenarios and benchmarking as needed and contribute to new business/expansion/process improvement as and when business requires.
B.skilled: 
Bachelor’s degree in Business, Finance, or other related field (preferred);
3+ years’ experience in a similar role;
Advanced knowledge of Excel;
Financial modeling and analytical skills;
Experience building dashboards with Tableau/Microstrategy
Knowledge of SQL, data mining and Microsoft VBA is preferred;
Strong in cooperating with different teams within our organization;
Strategic mindset and a strong desire to aid to data-driven decision making;
Able to tell the story from a detailed data rich landscape;
A problem solving mindset and providing the best analysis possible to the key decision makers;
Ability to listen, work with and proactively advise colleagues and business partners;
Strong team-working skills with ability to work independently;
Comfortable working in cross-functional teams and working in an unstructured environment;
Demonstrated ability to manage multiple competing priorities simultaneously and drive projects to completion.

